<L>__{exterior orchard day}
<A>__{babe brother and harry get out of the car. they walk on a path that takes them under low hanging tree limbs. it gets darker as they go deeper into the orchard. babe brother finds the going rough and loses his footing.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{give me your arm lest you fall.}
<A>__{harry has to help him stay on his feet. babe brother finds it necessary to take harry's arm. babe brother stops and harry walks a few more steps ahead and waits for babe brother. just ahead sitting on a branch is a huge white owl camouflaged by tree branches.}
<C>__{babe brother}
<D>__{i could swear i heard my son call me.}
<C>__{harry}
<D>__{you probably heard the wind stirring up those dead leaves over there.}
<C>__{babe brother}
<D>__{i heard his voice as clear as day. i better get back. maybe something is wrong.}
<A>__{babe brother turns and starts hurrying back before harry can object. he walks slowly after babe brother who is doubling the distance between himself and harry as he runs through the orchard to his car. harry stops and looks around.}
